50|$|Polygala senega is {{a species}} of {{flowering}} plant in the milkwort family, Polygalaceae. It is native to North America, where it is distributed in southern Canada and the central and eastern United States. Its common names include <b>Seneca</b> <b>snakeroot,</b> senega snakeroot, senegaroot, rattlesnake root, and mountain flax. Its species name honors the Seneca people, a Native American group who used the plant to treat snakebite.|$|E

